# Diacritics Fine-Tuning Code Conventions

## Project Scope

- Standalone project. Does NOT depend on Summa (the existing prompting-only diacritics repo).
- Handles both training and evaluation for Romanian diacritic restoration.

## Model Families

Three model families, all implemented as separate modules:
1. Lightweight supervised: character BiLSTM, CharCNN + BERT token classification
2. Sequence-to-sequence: ByT5, mT5
3. Decoder-only LLMs: LoRA and full fine-tuning on 1B-8B models (Gemma, Llama)

## Evaluation Requirements

Always report the full metric suite:
- Full-text word accuracy (WA) and character accuracy (CA)
- Diacritizable-word accuracy and diacritizable-character accuracy
- Diacritic Error Rate (DER)
- Hallucination rate (for generative models)
- Per-character F-scores for ă, â, î, ș, ț

## Experiment Design

- Noise robustness experiments: typos + casing + mixed diacritics
- Pre-1993 vs post-1993 orthography handled as separate evaluation conditions
- All experiments must log to `artifacts/` with timestamped directories

## Cross-References

- Paper repo: `diacritics-finetuning-paper`
- Prior work: `llm-diacritics-paper` and https://github.com/mihainadas/summa
